Step 5: Create reader.rs

Implement these functions:

pub fn read_csv(path: &str) -> Result<(CsvSchema, Vec<Vec<String>>), AppError>
  - Read CSV file using the csv crate
  - Return schema (columns + row count) and raw rows as Vec<Vec<String>>
  - Handle files with and without headers
  - Handle empty files gracefully

pub fn detect_primary_key_candidates(schema: &CsvSchema) -> Vec<String>
  - Suggest columns likely to be primary keys
  - Rules:
    1. Column name ends with _id, _key, _code, _uuid, _ref
    2. Column name is exactly: id, key, code, uuid, ref
    3. Case insensitive matching
  - Return column names sorted by confidence

pub fn detect_noise_columns(schema: &CsvSchema) -> Vec<String>
  - Suggest columns to ignore in diff
  - Rules: column name contains any of:
    created_at, updated_at, modified_at, created_date,
    updated_date, last_modified, insert_date, load_date,
    etl_timestamp, row_hash, checksum, modified_by
  - Case insensitive matching
  - Return matched column names

